      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can a probiotic really affect testosterone levels?",
            "answer": "<p>Directly? No — Origin doesn't contain testosterone or testosterone precursors. What it does is restore the gut bacterial ecosystem that regulates your body's own hormonal signaling pathway. Published research in <em>Gut Microbes</em> (Shin et al., 2019) demonstrates that gut bacteria modulate the hypothalamic-pituitary-gonadal (HPG) axis through short-chain fatty acid production. When that pathway functions correctly, your body is better positioned to produce testosterone naturally. Fix the gut. Let your biology do the rest.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long before I notice results?",
            "answer": "<p>Most men report the first noticeable change in energy within 2–4 weeks — this typically comes from reduced gut-driven systemic inflammation rather than any direct hormonal shift. Strength and recovery improvements tend to follow at 4–8 weeks as the bacterial ecosystem stabilizes. Lab-confirmed changes in testosterone markers, if measured, typically appear after 2–3 months of consistent use. Every biology is different, which is why we offer a 30-day money-back guarantee.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I take Origin alongside ashwagandha, tongkat ali, or other testosterone support supplements?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Origin doesn't conflict with adaptogens or testosterone-supporting botanicals. In fact, restoring gut health through Origin may improve the bioavailability and effectiveness of those supplements — since gut barrier integrity affects how well nutrients are absorbed in the first place. If you're on any prescription medications or existing hormone protocols, consult your physician before adding any supplement.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Why does ethnicity matter for gut health and hormones?",
            "answer": "<p>The HELIUS study — 2,084 subjects across 6 ethnic groups — proved that biological heritage is the strongest predictor of gut microbiome composition, stronger than diet, age, sex, or medical history. Ancestral bacterial populations that supported hormonal regulation for generations can deplete within a single generation of Western dietary exposure (Vangay et al., 2018). This isn't a lifestyle problem — it's a biological one with a biological solution.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What's in Origin and is it vegan?",
            "answer": "<p>Origin contains 40 Billion CFU across 4 clinically documented strains: L. acidophilus, B. lactis, L. plantarum, and L. paracasei. It uses MAKTREK Bi-Pass marine polysaccharide acid-protection delivery and FOS fructooligosaccharide prebiotic. Capsule shell is HPMC (hypromellose) — 100% vegan. No gelatin, no artificial fillers, no animal-derived ingredients. cGMP certified, made in USA.</p>"
          }
        }
